      • getSqlOffset

        public int getSqlOffset()
        Returns the SQL column starting position of this logical PGQL column in the column list of the SQL translation. OraclePgqlColumnDescriptor.Type.VERTEX and OraclePgqlColumnDescriptor.Type.EDGE PGQL columns have two corresponding SQL columns (column_name$IT, column_name$ID). OraclePgqlColumnDescriptor.Type.VALUE PGQL columns have four corresponding SQL columns (column_name$T, column_name$V, column_name$VN, column_name$VT). The offset starts from 1. That is, the first PGQL column has an offset of 1.
        Specified by:
        getSqlOffset in interface OraclePgqlColumnDescriptor
        Returns:
        the starting position of this logical PGQL column in the return columns of the SQL translation
